Why Catgirl?

Catgirl began as a joke on Twitter from Elon Musk, but soon turned into a vision combining anime, AI, and robotics. In 2024, Musk renewed the idea, saying catgirls in robot form are really coming, showing it was not just humor but a sketch of the future.

At Tesla’s 2022 AI Day, the Optimus robot revealed the potential of merging technology with creative design. Musk called anime-inspired humanoid robots “probably inevitable.” That inevitability sparked a movement blending innovation, culture, and community.

We believe memes are more than fun: they forecast cultural desires before the market notices them. Catgirl Robot is not just fantasy, but a new way to imagine human–machine interaction — a future where AI feels expressive, close, and inspired by people.

How To Buy

Download metamask or your wallet of choice from the app store or google play store for free. Desktop users, download the google chrome extension by going to metamask.io.

Have ETH in your wallet to switch to $CATGIRL. If you don’t have any ETH, you can buy directly on metamask, transfer from another wallet, or buy on another exchange and send it to your wallet.

Connect to Uniswap. Go to app.uniswap.org in google chrome or on the browser inside your Metamask app. Connect your wallet. Paste the $CATGIRL token address into Uniswap, select Catgirl, and confirm. When Metamask prompts you for a wallet signature, sign.

Swap ETH for $CATGIRL. We have ZERO taxes so you don’t need to worry about buying with a specific slippage, although you may need to use slippage during times of market volatility.
